    <PageTitle>FAQ about Neonatal Jaundice & BiliTool.Vn</PageTitle>

    <HeadContent>
        <meta name="description" content="Answers to common questions: BiliTool.Vn uses AAP 2022 guidelines, applies to infants ≥35 weeks gestation, requires Total Serum Bilirubin (TSB) without subtracting direct bilirubin, and can be integrated into electronic medical records (HIS/EMR)." />
        <meta name="keywords" content="FAQ neonatal jaundice, total serum bilirubin TSB, AAP 2022, 35 weeks gestation, HIS EMR integration bilitool" />
        <link rel="canonical" href="https://bilitool.vn/cau-hoi-thuong-gap" />
        <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
        <meta property="og:title" content="FAQ — Frequently Asked Questions | BiliTool.Vn" />
        <meta property="og:description" content="Answers to questions regarding the neonatal bilirubin calculation algorithm, AAP 2022 guidelines, and EMR integration." />
        <meta property="og:url" content="https://bilitool.vn/cau-hoi-thuong-gap" />
        <meta property="og:site_name" content="BiliTool.Vn" />
        <meta property="og:image" content="https://bilitool.vn/images/og-bilitool.png" />
        <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
        <meta name="twitter:title" content="FAQ — Neonatal Jaundice & BiliTool.Vn" />
        <meta name="twitter:description" content="Answers to common questions about neonatal bilirubin calculations and AAP 2022 guidelines." />
        <script type="application/ld+json">
        {
            "@@context": "https://schema.org",
            "@@type": "FAQPage",
            "mainEntity": [
                {
                    "@@type": "Question",
                    "name": "Where does BiliTool.Vn get its reference data?",
                    "acceptedAnswer": {
                        "@@type": "Answer",
                        "text": "BiliTool.Vn is built based on the Clinical Practice Guideline of the American Academy of Pediatrics (AAP) updated in 2022 combined with NICE CG98, using a cubic spline interpolation algorithm."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "@@type": "Question",
                    "name": "Which pediatric patients can be evaluated using this platform?",
                    "acceptedAnswer": {
                        "@@type": "Answer",
                        "text": "The recommendation and calculation on the system is only medically valid when applied to newborns with a gestational age of 35 weeks or older (≥ 35 weeks gestation). Preterm infants under 35 weeks gestation require separate protocols."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "@@type": "Question",
                    "name": "Is the entered laboratory value direct or total bilirubin?",
                    "acceptedAnswer": {
                        "@@type": "Answer",
                        "text": "AAP 2022 recommends using Total Serum Bilirubin (TSB). DO NOT subtract direct bilirubin from the total before entering it into the software."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "@@type": "Question",
                    "name": "Can I integrate this automated chart into my hospital's Electronic Medical Record?",
                    "acceptedAnswer": {
                        "@@type": "Answer",
                        "text": "Yes. BiliTool.Vn supports integration into HIS/EMR systems via two methods: Deep Link (URL parameters) and RESTful API (JSON). Details are in the HIS Integration section of the website."
                    }
                }
            ]
        }
        </script>
    </HeadContent>

    <div class="guide-wrapper">
        <div class="guide-header">
            <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
            <div>
                <h1>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h1>
                <p>Answers to questions related to the calculation algorithm</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="guide-content custom-faq">
            <section class="mb-5">
                <h2 class="faq-title">
                    <i class="fas fa-comments"></i> Common Questions
                </h2>
                
                <div class="faq-accordion shadow-sm">
                    
                    <details class="faq-item" open>
                        <summary class="faq-question">
                            <span>1. Where does BiliTool.Vn get its reference data?</span>
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>The calculation tool on BiliTool.Vn is completely free, translated, and mathematically modeled from a pure cubic spline interpolation algorithm to systematically and automatically reconstruct the **Clinical Practice Guideline of the American Academy of Pediatrics (AAP) updated in 2022**. In addition, the calculation structure of Age in Hours is also established according to Vietnamese medical regulations.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    
                    <details class="faq-item">
                        <summary class="faq-question">
                            <span>2. Which pediatric patients can be evaluated using this platform?</span>
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Calculations and representations on the system are medically valid only when applied to newborn infants with a **gestational age of 35 weeks or older (>= 35 weeks gestation)**. Preterm infants under 35 weeks gestational age have lower liver function and neurotoxicity thresholds; therefore, it is mandatory to use separate standard protocols, such as the low birth weight guidelines of the National Institute of Nutrition, the NICE charts in the UK, or the local standards of individual Neonatal Intensive Care Units (NICUs).</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    
                    <details class="faq-item">
                        <summary class="faq-question">
                            <span>3. Is the entered laboratory value direct or total bilirubin?</span>
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>The 2022 AAP update inherits a very important point from 2004: it recommends using the blood biochemical test value **Total Serum Bilirubin (TSB)** to input into the calculation tool. Please note: Even if Direct Bilirubin is elevated, you **DO NOT** need to and **MUST NOT** subtract the direct value from the TSB total before entering it into the software, to avoid misinterpreting the phototherapy indications for the patient.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    
                    <details class="faq-item">
                        <summary class="faq-question">
                            <span>4. Can I integrate this automated chart into my hospital's Electronic Medical Record?</span>
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>BiliTool.Vn supports a compatible module for embedding via iframe or pop-up link for Hospital Information Systems (HIS/EMR) through RESTful API protocols and Deep Link parameters via URL. This allows hospitals to transmit vital signs and laboratory results automatically instead of requiring users to type them manually. Please navigate to the <a href="/tich-hop-his" class="fw-bold faq-link">HIS Integration</a> tab on the menu to reference the technical documentation for developers.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-footer text-muted">
                    <p><i class="fas fa-info-circle me-1"></i> If you cannot find your question, please use the form in the <a href="/lien-he" class="fw-bold faq-link">Contact</a> section.</p>
                </div>
            </section>
        </div>
    </div>
}
